title: For Sale:  Moose/elk Hauler Snowplow forklift Custom 4 wheeler (Must See Hunt/work/fun money make - $4400
postcontent:
Would make an awesome snowplow or forklift and can be fun or moneymaker. Here is a unique opportunity to own one sweet custom ATV/Tractor/Log hauler or whatever kind of toy you want to call it. This was made to hunt moose up north. Everything is very neat and custom. The machine and fabrication work is quality and factory look Precise welds and cuts. 

Volvo B18 engine with the 2 SU carbs , with the M20 4 speed Volvo trans and clutch coupled to a GM 4 speed trans with a well made custom transfer case that drives the front and rear Chev HO 4.56:1 solid axles. THis gives you a perfect 4 speed with 4 different ranges. The trans has a PTO that drives a winch mounted up front. Also has front shaft in which you could run other equipment off of the PTO. The steering is completely hydraulic with all new components and lines that run to the front and rear hydraulic rams. There is a switch panel with ign. key switch,switches and gauges for oil and fluid pressures. The frame is well made and houses the oil for the hydraulics. There is a drive shaft brake lever operated as an ebrake. The brakes are drums Chev.on all on all 4 wheels but are not hooked up yet to the master cylinder. The tall tractor tires are mounted on custom rims said to be of aircraft origin. There is another set of wheels and tires that go along with the package, that aid in transportation. Actually thought lower wheels would be great if you are not at all into the monster truck look. Dually wheels on both axles would be great. ITs a versatile machine that can have many uses. The Winch is awesome with all new cable.

Pull logs out, run a log splitter, put a snow plow on it, build a custom cab over it and have the best looking and versatile 4 wheeler. ITs more then a 4 wheeler and there is very expensive components that went into this. A true workhorse that will last you a long time. I have got this sweet machine running and all the hydraulics hooked up. Very little to do. I think it might be possible with Street tires to customize it for street use. Like a homebuilt/experimental automobile. Not sure about that but it has many other uses besides that.

Open to trades. Let me know what you have.
